  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-3.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Path Optimality Criterion</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-3.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall define path optimality as minimizing the total path length measured as the sum of Euclidean or Manhattan distances between successive waypoints, depending on the configured grid connectivity.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-3.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Shortest Path Algorithm</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-PLAN-3.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-PLAN-3.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall use a complete shortest-path search algorithm, such as A* or Dijkstra's Algorithm, to compute an optimal path on the grid from a specified start cell to a specified target cell.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-3.1.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Handling Unreachable Targets</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      If the planner cannot find a collision-free path to the requested target cell, the system shall report the target as unreachable and trigger selection of an alternative reachable target or terminate exploration based on current state.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-PLAN-3.1.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Path Replanning on Map Updates</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-3.1</Refines>
