    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-4.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL-RUN-4.1.3</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      After successfully reaching the start pose at the end of exploration, the system shall transition from RETURN_TO_START to SECOND_RUN state without resetting the internal maze representation.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-4.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Target Selection for Second Run</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-4.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-3.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      At the beginning of the SECOND_RUN state, the system shall select a predefined target cell within the maze, such as the maze goal cell, based on configuration or competition rules.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-4.3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Efficient Path Computation for Second Run</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-4.3</Refines>
