    <ItemID>LL-EXPL-1.2.0.1</ItemID>
    <Severity>Major</Severity>
    <Description>
      LL-EXPL-1.2.0.1 defines transitions between IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, and SECOND_RUN but does not specify transitions out of RETURN_TO_START in abnormal cases (e.g., failure to reach the start pose within a configured timeout, or path planning failure) nor transitions back to IDLE when exploration is aborted due to severe faults or safe-stop conditions. This leaves the state machine behavior incomplete for error and abort scenarios, which is needed for consistent architecture design.
    </Description>
    <Solution>
      Add one or more LLRs under the EXPL/RUN/RELIAB categories to define:
      (a) transitions to an explicit aborted/idle state when RETURN_TO_START cannot be completed (e.g., timeout, unreachable start), and
