      <DependsOn>LL-RUN-4.1.4</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL-RUN-4.1.5</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall implement the following state transitions: from IDLE to EXPLORE when the exploration start condition is met; from EXPLORE to RETURN_TO_START when exploration is marked as done; from RETURN_TO_START to SECOND_RUN when the robot reaches the start pose within the configured tolerance and no abort condition has been raised; from SECOND_RUN to IDLE when the second run is declared complete; and from RETURN_TO_START or SECOND_RUN back to IDLE when a path execution abort condition is raised or a severe fault causes a safe stop that is followed by a system reset.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

