    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall implement the following state transitions based on path execution status signals: from IDLE to EXPLORE when the exploration start condition is met; from EXPLORE to RETURN_TO_START when exploration is marked as done; from RETURN_TO_START to SECOND_RUN when a PATH_COMPLETED status for the return path is received and no PATH_ABORTED status has been raised; from SECOND_RUN to IDLE when a PATH_COMPLETED status for the second-run path is received; and from RETURN_TO_START or SECOND_RUN back to IDLE when a PATH_ABORTED status is raised or a severe fault causes a safe stop that is followed by a system reset.
    </Content>
